The paper deals with face recognition and privacy, which are both topics that fall under computer vision (cs.CV) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The use of soft-biometrics and templates also suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM). The proposed approach involves representing face templates in a negative domain, which could involve machine learning techniques such as generative models (cs.LG) or information retrieval (cs.IR).
